Content:
The Enchanting Verses is a poetry e-magazine based in West Bengal, India. Since 2008 the magazine has published three to four issues per year featuring poetic works of both new and established poets. Some of the notable contributors to this magazine include Malay Roy Choudhury, Gopi Kottoor, K. Satchidanandan, Candice James, Rita Dahl, Taslima Nasrin, Hemant Divate, Kishwar Naheed and Nathalie Handal.[1] The Enchanting Verses collaborated with the oldest literary magazine of Macedonia named Stremez in March 2011 to contribute to cultural exchange through poetry between Macedonia and the rest of the world.[2][3][4][5] The journal bestows the title of The Enchanting Poet per issue to a poet in recognition to his contributions to the world of poetry. Some of the notable recipients of this include Jayanta Mahapatra, Mateja Matevski, Dimitris P. Kraniotis, Jovica Tasevski-Eternijan, Stephen Gill, Dorin Popa, Dariusz Pacak, Ram Krishna Singh and Patricia Prime.[6][7]
